<table class="drug-table data-table table table-condensed table-bordered"><tbody><tr id="identification"><th class="divider" colspan="2">Identification</th></tr><tr><th>Name</th><td><strong>Scopolamine</strong></td></tr><tr><th>Accession Number</th><td><strong>DB00747</strong>&#160; (APRD00616)</td></tr><tr><th>Type</th><td>small molecule</td></tr><tr><th>Groups</th><td>approved</td></tr><tr><th>Description</th><td><p>An alkaloid from Solanaceae, especially Datura metel L. and Scopola carniolica. Scopolamine and its quaternary derivatives act as antimuscarinics like atropine, but may have more central nervous system effects. Among the many uses are as an anesthetic premedication, in urinary incontinence, in motion sickness, as an antispasmodic, and as a mydriatic and cycloplegic. [PubChem]</p></td></tr><tr><th>Structure</th><td><div class="structure"><a class="moldbi-thumbnail" href="http://structures.wishartlab.com/molecules/DB00747/image.png"><img alt="Thumb" src="http://structures.wishartlab.com/molecules/DB00747/thumb.png"></a></div><div class="structure-links"><div class="btn-group btn-group-xs"><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00747.mol">MOL</a><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00747.sdf">SDF</a><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00747.pdb">PDB</a><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00747.smiles">SMILES</a><a class="btn btn-default" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00747.inchi">InChI</a><a class="btn btn-info" href="/structures/structures/small_molecule_drugs/DB00747">View Structure</a></div></div></td></tr><tr><th>Synonyms</th><td class="data-table-container"><table class="table table-condensed table-striped datatable" id="synonyms"><thead><th>Synonym</th><th>Language</th><th>Code</th></thead><tbody><tr><td>(-)-hyoscine</td><td><span class="wishart wishart-not-avail